{
    "abstract": "We present a new approach for adding Bernoulli beam reinforcements to Kirchhoff plates. The plate is discretised using a continuous/discontinuous finite element method based on standard continuous piecewise polynomial finite element spaces. The beams are discretised by the CutFEM technique of letting the basis functions of the plate represent also the beams which are allowed to pass through the plate elements. This allows for a fast and easy way of assessing where the plate should be supported, for instance, in an optimization loop.",
    "author_highlights": [
        {
            "endOffset": 111054,
            "sentence": "We present a new approach for combining 2D plate and 1D beam models for reinforced structures.",
            "startOffset": 110960
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 111137,
            "sentence": "The plate and beam models use the same discontinuous finite element approximation.",
            "startOffset": 111055
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 111201,
            "sentence": "The beams can intersect the plate mesh in an arbitrary fashion.",
            "startOffset": 111138
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 111268,
            "sentence": "Beam stiffness is added to plate stiffness in the discrete system.",
            "startOffset": 111202
        }
    ],
