            "secId": "sec3.2",
            "sentence": "The idea of using continuous/discontinuous approximations was first proposed by Engel et al. [6] and later analysed for Kirchhoff\u2013Love and Mindlin\u2013Reissner plates in Refs. [7,9,10], cf. also Wells and Dung [21].",
